notes.text:
Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform release 3.11.59 is now available with
updates to packages and images that fix several bugs and add enhancements.
notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform is Red Hat's cloud computing
Kubernetes application platform solution designed for on-premise or private
cloud deployments.

This advisory contains the RPM packages for Red Hat OpenShift Container
Platform 3.11.59. See the following advisory for the container images for
this release:

https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHBA-2019:0023

Space precludes documenting all of the bug fixes and enhancements in this
advisory. See the following Release Notes documentation, which will be
updated shortly for this release, for details about these changes:

https://docs.openshift.com/container-platform/3.11/release_notes/ocp_3_11_release_notes.html

All OpenShift Container Platform 3.11 users are advised to upgrade to these
updated packages and images.

notes.text: A code execution vulnerability exists in the Stapler web framework used by Jenkins 2.153 and earlier, LTS 2.138.3 and earlier in stapler/core/src/main/java/org/kohsuke/stapler/MetaClass.java that allows attackers to invoke some methods on Java objects by accessing crafted URLs that were not intended to be invoked this way.
notes.title: Vulnerability description

notes.text: jenkins: code execution through crafted URLs (SECURITY-595)
notes.title: Vulnerability summary

notes.text: This vulnerability is only exploitable by a user with developer permissions. Therefore this vulnerability is rated Important for OpenShift Container Platform 3.x.
notes.title: Statement

notes.text: The CVSS score(s) listed for this vulnerability do not reflect the associated product's status, and are included for informational purposes to better understand the severity of this vulnerability.
notes.title: CVSS score applicability

notes.text: An information exposure vulnerability exists in Jenkins 2.153 and earlier, LTS 2.138.3 and earlier in DirectoryBrowserSupport.java that allows attackers with the ability to control build output to browse the file system on agents running builds beyond the duration of the build using the workspace browser.
notes.title: Vulnerability description

notes.text: jenkins: workspace browser allowed accessing files outside the workspace (SECURITY-904)

notes.text: A data modification vulnerability exists in Jenkins 2.153 and earlier, LTS 2.138.3 and earlier in User.java, IdStrategy.java that allows attackers to submit crafted user names that can cause an improper migration of user record storage formats, potentially preventing the victim from logging into Jenkins.
